title: Leopard_Start
---
A spotted leopard slips between the trees, light-footed and quick. It blocks the path and circles you.
<<fight_start>>
===


title: Leopard_Study
---
You watch the leopard's restless circling, trying to read it.
It darts in before you finish the thought.
<<fight_dodge "leopard_pounce">>
<<if fight_hp() <= 0>>
    <<fight_end "lose">>
<<else>>
    You learn its rhythm, but watching alone changes nothing. It paces, waiting.
    <<fight_menu>>
<<endif>>
===


title: Leopard_Provoke
---
You shout and stamp to drive the beast off.
The leopard takes it as a game and pounces harder.
<<fight_dodge "leopard_flurry">>
<<if fight_hp() <= 0>>
    <<fight_end "lose">>
<<else>>
    The provocation only sharpens its excitement. It will not be scared away.
    <<fight_menu>>
<<endif>>
===


title: Leopard_MatchPace
---
You slow your breathing and let your steps fall into the leopard's own restless rhythm; moving with it, not against it.
<<fight_dodge "leopard_pounce">>
<<if fight_hp() <= 0>>
    <<fight_end "lose">>
<<else>>
    The frantic circling eases. Curiosity replaces the hunger in its eyes, and it sits, tail flicking.
    <<fight_spare_enable>>
    <<fight_menu>>
<<endif>>
===


title: Leopard_Win
---
The leopard dips its head once, then melts back into the green shadow of the wood. The path ahead is clear.
===


title: Leopard_Lose
---
The leopard is too quick, too light. Your strength fails and the dark wood closes over you.
===
